title: For Trade:  WTT 1954 IHC Complete M1 Garand 30 06 rifle
postcontent:
Trade only at this time. I have a very nice M1 Garand with an LMR barrel graded at 1.75 MZ and 1.0 TE plus extras like GI cleaning kit extra clips and GI pouches. Certified from CMP.  IHC parts including trigger group from CMP that I'm considering trading for a colt snake gun or multiple colt 1911's. 

To answer some of the PMs coming in, here's the value assessment for trade.

As far as value - looking at the Garand Collector's Association model for placing value on Garands, they have a forumula utilizing a base price method and factors.  Current base price change occurred in 2013 to a base price of $700 for a 'model garand'. They then apply a multiplier factor to that $700 based on year made, manufacture, and type of Garand.  For this one, IHC with LMR barrel, the factor ranges from 4 to 7.  Therefore a retail range would be $2800 to $4900 in retail value based on the GCA scoring.  For trade value that would be near the range I'd be looking to hit, or a little less (so multiple 1911's such as a Gold Cup National Match, Gold Cup Trophy in stainless, a colt python, multiple colt cobra/DS's, colt anaconda, colt diamondback, etc) that would be valued in that range is what I'm looking for.

Add 15 enblocs plus over 200 rounds ammo which adds to the value too.



PM me for options.  Many pix available, including a copy of the article from the GCA Journel from Winter 2013 which I cannot publish here since I don't have permission.  Thanks for looking.

From SKDTAC's website:

Zero Tolerance 0360.SKD Knife, Folder w/ SpeedSafe, Carbide Tip
by Joe
Zero Tolerance 0360.SKD Knife *An SKD Exclusive!*- Of coursed this is a biased review, but if it gets carried daily, it deserves mention. The Zero Tolerance 0360.SKD & the ALL-NEW 0360.SKD are by far the best combination of practicality, strength, speed and quality I've ever carried in a folding knife- period. I was a fan of ZT quality before conceiving this model, but the 0300 series was not very practical for daily carry for me due to the width. The 0350 was a quantum leap in EDC practicality, but was still a bit wide in it's profile when folded. The ZT 0360.SKD manages to shave width and weight- one of the coolest thing you notice is the increase in opening speed when compared side by side with the 0350. I'm still trying to abuse it when I can, and it's still holding an awesome edge. When it opens and locks up, it is simply a FISTFUL OF AWESOME. The tastefully installed Carbide Tip Glass Breaker is the ultimate vehicle extrication insurance policy. This latest production 0360.SKD is the first ZT folder EVER to offer 2 (TWO!) pocket clips from the factory and a factory Torx Wrench. View More SKD Staff Picks

The ZT 0360.SKD represents 18 months of collaborative efforts between SKD and Zero Tolerance that started back in August of 2008. Initially based on the ZT 0300 series knives, the concept morphed and gained momentum with the release of the ZT 0350, and eventually migrating to the 0350 platform as the foundation for this new model. In technical parlance, we took a kick-ass knife, and made it KICK MORE ASS. Since our initial short production run back in 2010, there were key personnel changes at ZT and increases in minimum order requirements that made a follow-on production run somewhat elusive. Thanks to some help from Ms. Jennifer Newsome at ZT, and some good ole' grass-roots encouragement from fans at Bladeforums.com, we were able to secure a second production run and introduce a new Tiger Stripe model (0360TS.SKD). 

The 0360.SKD blade is a full 30% lighter than the 0350 blade, which results in a lighter overall weight and a dramatic increase in opening speed. The high-protein low-carb blade profile gives the 0360.SKD a leaner look than the 0350, without compromising strength- the blade thickness on both models is identical. 

The ZT SpeedSafe system makes for easy one-handed assisted opening even when wearing gloves. A small carbide tip is pressed into place at the butt of the handle for emergency glass-breaking use- this capability was put to the test with an actual vehicle extrication by one of our LEO customers! The blade is S30V stainless steel with Tungsten DLC (Diamond Like Carbon) means that the extremely durable corrosion resistant blade is further coated in a non-reflective self-lubricating corrosion resistant finish, so it isn't likely to corrode. Textured, matte-black G-10 scales provide a secure Kung-Fu grip. Includes a quad mounting array for tip-up, tip-down, left- or right-handed clip carry, and all 0360.SKD knives now ship with 2 (TWO!) Pocket Clips and a factory Torx wrench for Dual Clip carry as featured by Military Morons. 

This special edition ZT knife is only available at SKD, and each blade features a unique 3 digit serial number sequence. We ask that anyone planning on buying this knife actually use it- don't be a Nancy and make this a pocket queen. If we see any of these out there without any actual signs of real use, we will revoke your tough-guy card and reclaim our product in the dead of night.
